msContents.summary: Collection of ten religious plays by Calderón. There is a list of contents at the beginning (f. i recto). Numbers 4, 8 and 9 have the note "sub correctione S.R.E." in red at the end.

msItem.title: List of contents, f. i recto
El valle de la Zarzuela, f. 49r
El segundo blasson del Austria, f. 79r
El arbol de mejor fruto, f. 181r
No ay mas fortuna que dios, f. 225r

supportDesc.extent: 314 leaves : 208 x 152 (171 x 50) mm. bound to 220 x 165 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 312 + i (contemporary paper); [i], 1-311; contemporary foliation in ink, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by several different hands.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illustrated initial "S" in red and yellow (f. 1r); drawing in red (f. 223r); extensive use of red to indicate speakers, stage directions, etc.
Historiated initial, Village scene, Initial S, f. 1r

binding.p: Contemporary parchment. Some stains. Cover is almost entirely separated from text block. One gathering at the beginning (f. i-6) is completely detached.

history.provenance: Former owners include: Convent "A Franca" (note, f. i recto); Hugo Albert Rennert (bookplate, inside upper cover).
